cat /etc/hosts
cat /etc/resolv.conf
sudo netplan apply
sudo netplan generate
sudo netplan try
sudo netplan status
this can run in CentOS, openSUSE,RHEL etc

ping (test connectivity to a remote host)
ifconfig (configure network interfaces) (deprecated)
ip (manage network interfaces, ip address and routes)
netstat (display network connection) important)
ss (socket statistic)
